why do we use them, what do they tell

00:00:55.240 --> 00:00:57.580
us about the English language, what

00:00:57.620 --> 00:00:59.900
are some of the euphemisms you need

00:00:59.900 --> 00:01:02.869
to know, and what are some unusual

